**Available for "The AcademicYear" which would be SEPT. 2022 through MAY 2023**<br>
This is NOT a year round rental.<br>
$1,150/Month<br>
Tenant pays heat (electric) and electricity and trash pick up..<br>
Owner pays WiFi, metered water and yard maintenance.<br>
<br>
*Please Include Contact Name And Number With Inquiry... for a reply*<br>
<br>
This FULLY Furnished cozy year round beach home has two bedrooms - 1 queen-sized memory foam bed and 2 twin beds in the other.<br>
Mattresses and pillows are encased in covers.<br>
The living room has a comfy couch, love seat, chairs, and a large flat screen Smart t.v.<br>
The kitchen is well-equipped with every gadget you could need and a generous assortment of pots, pans and bake ware. Located off the kitchen is a cheery 4-season porch. A dining table and comfy furniture make this the perfect spot to curl up with a good book or relax with friends for coffee and conversation.<br>
Located off the mudroom is an outside patio with a table and chairs and a gas grill, the perfect spot to relax and grill after a fun day at the beach. The back yard is spacious and inviting. The outside shower has hot and cold running water.<br>
The flat, level neighborhood is perfect for leisurely afternoon walks and bike riding.<br>
Two beautiful private sandy beaches are just a short 5 minute stroll down lovely tree-lined roads. One of the beaches boasts a waterfront gazebo and a long winding jetty with benches along the flat top for admiring the scenic panoramic views of Long Island Sound. There is also a small playground and grassy area for beach play. The other private beach is very spacious as well and has lovely scenic views of Long Island Sound.<br>
Easy access to I-95 and Rte 9, Saybrook Center Boutiques and "The Kate", Boston Post Road shops and a variety of Ethnic Restaurants, Westbook and Clinton Shopping Outlets and The Casinos! Watch Hill, Rhode Island and it's infamous oldest running Carousel are just a 45 minute drive away.<br>
The area is quiet and calming yet quickly accessible to many restaurants and entertainment.<br>
No Pets<br>
No Smoking, Vaping Etc.<br>
*PLEASE INCLUDE A CONTACT NUMBER WITH YOUR INQUIRY.<br>
Academic Rental $1,150/month<br>
<br>
Summer Rental: $1,375.00 per wk. Certain weeks still available August 2022.<br>
<br>
